# Antigravity CLI (`agy`) — delivery + execute manifest. The headline third-party
# proof harness: registered once, works as BOTH an install target and an executor,
# with no Antigravity-specific engine code beyond its hook I/O adapter.
#
# hook archetype: live per-model-call injection via a PreInvocation hook in
# Antigravity's hooks.json (harnesses/antigravity/hooks/preinvocation.sh) — the
# same live-refresh model as Claude, NOT a materialized file. xml format: the
# injected payload is the <memory:*> serialization, identical to Claude's.
name           = antigravity
archetype      = hook
format         = xml

# hook registration: Antigravity discovers hooks from a JSON file at its global
# customization root (~/.gemini/config/). The install driver registers a namespaced
# PreInvocation entry (hook_script, live memory injection) and a PreToolUse entry
# (guard_script, executor-only enforcement). (Contrast Claude's hooks_dir
# script-symlink + settings.json model.) $MEMORY_DIR is expanded at install time so
# the commands have stable absolute paths.
hooks_json     = ~/.gemini/config/hooks.json
hook_script    = $MEMORY_DIR/harnesses/antigravity/hooks/preinvocation.sh
guard_script   = $MEMORY_DIR/harnesses/antigravity/hooks/pretooluse.sh

# Skills: Antigravity honors the cross-agent ~/.agents/skills standard (it is
# listed in ~/.agents/.skill-lock.json), and its skill layout is skills/<name>/
# SKILL.md — byte-identical to our canonical store, so fan-out is a zero-transform
# symlink. commands=skill: Antigravity's command mechanism IS skills.
skills_dir     = ~/.agents/skills
commands       = skill

# execute face — headless `agy -p` via the launch wrapper. agy.sh exports the
# resolved project into agy's env, so the PreInvocation hook injects fresh memory
# for a delegated run. {prompt}/{model} substituted by executor.sh; $MEMORY_DIR
# expanded; exec_probe gates availability on the agy bin.
#
# exec_readonly is the SAME command: `agy -p` has no read-only CLI flag, so the
# read-only guarantee comes from the PreToolUse guard (guard_script) denying every
# non-read tool when executor.sh sets AI_MEMORY_ROLE=explore. This makes Antigravity
# a real `explore` executor (no longer degrading to the Claude Explore agent).
exec_cmd        = $MEMORY_DIR/harnesses/antigravity/scripts/agy.sh -p {prompt} --dangerously-skip-permissions
exec_readonly   = $MEMORY_DIR/harnesses/antigravity/scripts/agy.sh -p {prompt} --dangerously-skip-permissions
exec_model_flag = --model {model}
exec_probe      = agy
